opennlp.ccg.util.Filter

Packages that use Filter
opennlp.ccg.disjunctivizer Package for the disjunctivizer, which creates a disjunctive LF XML structure based on an LFGraphDifference. 
opennlp.ccg.util   
 

Uses of Filter in opennlp.ccg.disjunctivizer
 

Classes in opennlp.ccg.disjunctivizer that implement Filter
 class AlignedEdgeFilter
          A filter for edges that tests whether they are aligned based on a specified set of alignment indices.
 class EdgeMatchFilter
          A filter for LF edges based on a set of match type criteria.
 class LabelMatchFilter
          A filter for edges based on a comparison of their labels.
 class MatchTypeFilter
          Abstract class for filters that allow LFEdges based on criteria indicated by the set of match types they use.
 class VertexMatchFilter
          A filter that matches vertices based on a basis vertex and a set of match type criteria.

Uses of Filter in opennlp.ccg.util
 

Classes in opennlp.ccg.util that implement Filter
 class CompositeFilter<E>
          Composes the effects of several filters into a single filter.
 class DelegatedFilter<E,D>
          Abstract class for filters that delegates to another filter that tests elements that do not necessarily apply to the same type of elements as this filter.
 class InverseFilter<E>
          A filter that wraps another filter an inverts its effects.
 class MembershipFilter<E>
          A filter that allows elements based on their membership in a set specified at creation.
 class VisitedFilter<E>
          A filter that tracks which elements have already been visited by some process or iteration, allowing only those that have not yet been visited.
